1
00:00:10,468 --> 00:00:12,470
[grandiose, dramatic music playing]

2
00:00:16,557 --> 00:00:18,934
[Wednesday] <i>William Faulkner said,
"The past is never dead."</i>

3
00:00:18,934 --> 00:00:20,018
[thunder rumbling]

4
00:00:20,019 --> 00:00:21,812
<i>"It's not even the past."</i>

5
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:25,024
<i>In fact, it's all still happening.</i>

6
00:00:26,317 --> 00:00:28,777
<i>If Isaac's goal is to save his sister,</i>

7
00:00:30,612 --> 00:00:32,280
<i>why kidnap Pugsley?</i>

8
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:33,990
[man] All right. Spread out, guys.

9
00:00:33,991 --> 00:00:35,826
- You, that way.
- [woman] Pugsley!

10
00:00:35,826 --> 00:00:37,869
[Wednesday] <i>What does
a brain-eating genius need</i>

11
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:39,956
<i>with my half-wit brother?</i>

12
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:44,250
No sign of your son.

13
00:00:44,252 --> 00:00:47,087
- [Morticia exhales sharply]
- Any idea why someone would kidnap him?

14
00:00:47,088 --> 00:00:48,881
It's a total mystery, Sheriff.

15
00:00:48,881 --> 00:00:51,841
Can you think of anyone
who has a grudge against your family?

16
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:53,551
Could this be some kind of revenge?

17
00:00:53,552 --> 00:00:56,139
Are you blaming us
for our son's kidnapping?

18
00:00:57,015 --> 00:00:59,015
The search parties
will run through the night.

19
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:02,143
Parents who were at the gala
have already left with their kids.

20
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:03,686
All other students will be packed up

21
00:01:03,688 --> 00:01:06,106
and on their way home
by tomorrow afternoon.

22
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:09,819
I'm sorry. We're doing everything we can.

23
00:01:10,861 --> 00:01:14,031
[Morticia] I sent your father and Lurch
out to join the search parties.

24
00:01:14,031 --> 00:01:15,406
They won't find Pugsley.

25
00:01:15,408 --> 00:01:16,700
Isaac's too smart.

26
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:20,704
You need to work together, and to pool
your psychic abilities to locate him.

27
00:01:20,704 --> 00:01:22,873
My mother is a Dove
who's blind to malevolence,

28
00:01:22,873 --> 00:01:26,543
and my psychic ability is currently
on an unauthorized leave of absence.

29
00:01:27,712 --> 00:01:31,423
That's why you must turn
to the <i>other</i> Raven in your family.

30
00:01:31,424 --> 00:01:32,466
My mother?

31
00:01:32,466 --> 00:01:35,343
These are desperate times.

32
00:01:35,344 --> 00:01:37,889
[wry, impish music playing]

33
00:01:44,228 --> 00:01:47,814
Mama, I appreciate you
coming back on such short notice.

34
00:01:47,816 --> 00:01:50,734
Why would anyone
bother kidnapping Pugsley?

35
00:01:50,734 --> 00:01:52,944
Not to cast aspersions,

36
00:01:52,945 --> 00:01:55,614
but I know higher value corpses
than that boy.

37
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:57,950
His kidnapper
isn't looking for ransom money.

38
00:01:58,450 --> 00:02:01,912
He's being used as a pawn
to keep us away, or a ploy to draw us in.

39
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:06,626
So many delightful memories of this room.

40
00:02:07,334 --> 00:02:10,211
I can still hear
the terrified shrieks of my classmates

41
00:02:10,212 --> 00:02:12,881
during Rotwood's
Advanced Possession Class.

42
00:02:12,882 --> 00:02:14,508
[Hester chuckles]

43
00:02:14,509 --> 00:02:16,051
Scaredy-cats.

44
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:19,513
[Morticia exhales]

45
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:21,598
[eerie music playing]

46
00:02:23,810 --> 00:02:26,396
This does require
actual physical connection.

47
00:02:33,777 --> 00:02:37,281
Now we must clear our minds
of all past grievances.

48
00:02:37,281 --> 00:02:40,533
My past grievances are like fine wine.
They get better with age.

49
00:02:40,534 --> 00:02:41,618
Likewise.

50
00:02:45,456 --> 00:02:47,832
<i>Doves and Ravens together ignite</i>

51
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:51,461
<i>With wings of darkness and piercing eyes</i>

52
00:02:52,004 --> 00:02:54,923
<i>Guide us to truth through night and morn</i>

53
00:02:54,924 --> 00:02:57,968
<i>To this let our powers be sworn</i>

54
00:02:57,968 --> 00:03:00,137
I didn't drive all this way
to hold hands in the dark.

55
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:02,264
How long do we have to keep this up?

56
00:03:02,264 --> 00:03:05,310
Mama! For once just be quiet.
We're trying to find Pugsley.

57
00:03:07,103 --> 00:03:08,103
I feel something.

58
00:03:08,103 --> 00:03:10,605
- I feel it too.
- Do you sense it, Wednesday?

59
00:03:10,606 --> 00:03:13,484
[ominous music building]

60
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,323
[scraping in distance]

61
00:03:20,991 --> 00:03:22,117
Hurry, Gomez!

62
00:03:24,412 --> 00:03:26,622
No one will ever know we were here.

63
00:03:32,628 --> 00:03:34,631
[jauntily macabre intro music playing]

64
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:36,483
[music trails off]

65
00:04:37,401 --> 00:04:38,569
[gasps]

66
00:04:39,444 --> 00:04:41,822
I saw you and Father
burying Isaac under the Skull Tree

67
00:04:41,822 --> 00:04:43,824
back when you were students.

68
00:04:45,701 --> 00:04:48,829
If there was ever a time to unburden
yourself of the truth, now is it.

69
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:55,793
You've wasted enough of my time.

70
00:04:55,795 --> 00:04:57,170
The night of Isaac's accident,

71
00:04:58,088 --> 00:04:59,590
your father and I

72
00:05:00,257 --> 00:05:02,050
were at his laboratory

73
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:04,927
in Iago Tower.

74
00:05:04,928 --> 00:05:07,596
[gloomy, dramatic music playing]

75
00:05:07,598 --> 00:05:12,269
<i>Isaac was certain his machine
would permanently cure Francoise.</i>

76
00:05:12,269 --> 00:05:15,480
<i>That she would never again
live in fear of turning into a Hyde.</i>

77
00:05:16,606 --> 00:05:21,278
<i>But the machine required
a great amount of energy to power it.</i>

78
00:05:21,903 --> 00:05:23,404
And for that,

79
00:05:23,406 --> 00:05:25,949
Isaac turned to his best friend.

80
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:27,367
Father.

81
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:34,000
What could Gomez
have possibly contributed?

82
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:39,213
[Morticia] <i>Back then,
Gomez was just as electrifying as Pugsley.</i>

83
00:05:40,255 --> 00:05:43,884
<i>And Gomez was more than happy
to help his friend.</i>

84
00:05:43,884 --> 00:05:46,303
But Isaac tricked him.

85
00:05:48,096 --> 00:05:50,057
<i>He needed more than a spark.</i>

86
00:05:53,935 --> 00:05:55,312
<i>Unbeknownst to Francoise,</i>

87
00:05:55,312 --> 00:05:59,399
<i>Isaac was willing to sacrifice
your father's life to save hers.</i>

88
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:02,401
He even dug your father's grave

89
00:06:02,403 --> 00:06:04,779
under the Skull Tree in preparation.

90
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:06,783
[dramatic music intensifies]

91
00:06:08,617 --> 00:06:09,576
[screaming]

92
00:06:16,584 --> 00:06:18,250
[Morticia] <i>By the time I arrived,</i>

93
00:06:18,252 --> 00:06:21,213
my darling Gomez was close to death.

94
00:06:22,005 --> 00:06:26,593
My sabotage
sent the machine into a frenzy.

95
00:06:36,228 --> 00:06:38,521
Francoise, she survived the explosion,

96
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:39,606
but Isaac didn't.

97
00:06:40,316 --> 00:06:42,233
<i>And as for your father,</i>

98
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:46,613
<i>the experience permanently robbed him
of his Outcast ability.</i>

99
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:49,449
Hmm.

100
00:06:50,659 --> 00:06:51,659
Why cover it up?

101
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:53,829
Because Augustus Stonehurst threatened us.

102
00:06:53,829 --> 00:06:55,997
We knew he built Isaac the lab in secret.

103
00:06:55,997 --> 00:06:58,875
If we breathed a word,
he would've turned us in for murder.

104
00:06:58,875 --> 00:07:00,168
Hurry, Gomez.

105
00:07:01,586 --> 00:07:03,423
No one will ever know we were here.

106
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:07,343
So you buried Isaac
in the same grave he intended for Father?

107
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:12,932
Yes.

108
00:07:13,557 --> 00:07:15,100
Isaac must be trying again.

109
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:17,394
This time using
Pugsley as the power source.

110
00:07:17,394 --> 00:07:20,189
That Addams headstone,
the one I saw in my premonition,

111
00:07:20,689 --> 00:07:21,898
must have Pugsley's name on it.

112
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:23,317
[sighs]

113
00:07:24,401 --> 00:07:29,113
I think it's best that you and Thing
go with Grandmama until Pugsley is found.

114
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:31,992
For once, your mother and I
are in agreement.

115
00:07:31,992 --> 00:07:34,661
[Morticia] These are our sins, Wednesday.

116
00:07:34,661 --> 00:07:36,038
We will face them.

117
00:07:37,706 --> 00:07:39,415
I won't put you in danger again.

118
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:40,500
Too late.

119
00:07:59,603 --> 00:08:00,605
[Ajax] I'm sorry.

120
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:03,524
You deserve better than that.

121
00:08:06,276 --> 00:08:08,487
[Enid] I didn't realize
we were back on speaking terms.

122
00:08:08,487 --> 00:08:10,072
It took me a minute.

123
00:08:11,115 --> 00:08:12,199
But I'm ready to be friends.

124
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:16,120
If that's cool with you.

125
00:08:18,497 --> 00:08:19,999
I'd like that very much.

126
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:23,543
Why the change of heart?

127
00:08:23,543 --> 00:08:25,879
[sweet, gentle music playing]

128
00:08:25,879 --> 00:08:28,298
I realized that
our breakup wasn't about me.

129
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,468
You know, it's nobody's fault
that your feelings changed.

130
00:08:32,052 --> 00:08:36,057
So I can either be angry about it,
or I can just accept it and move on.

131
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:39,392
Actually, Bianca told me that.

132
00:08:39,393 --> 00:08:40,476
[both chuckle]

133
00:08:40,477 --> 00:08:42,312
She can be very persuasive.

134
00:08:58,828 --> 00:08:59,788
[exhales]

135
00:08:59,788 --> 00:09:00,996
[gasps]

136
00:09:00,998 --> 00:09:04,625
Please tell me that you're done
with lying wolves and beta-gorgons.

137
00:09:04,626 --> 00:09:06,753
I put together
a list of potential boyfriends.

138
00:09:06,754 --> 00:09:10,298
I already cross-referenced them
based on compatible social media profiles.

139
00:09:10,298 --> 00:09:12,008
Once you've narrowed it down,

140
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:14,677
I can pay each one an invisible visit.

141
00:09:14,678 --> 00:09:17,013
See what they've left out of their bios.

142
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:18,181
Hmm.

143
00:09:18,182 --> 00:09:19,975
I appreciate the assist,

144
00:09:20,475 --> 00:09:24,104
but I think I'm gonna rip a page
out of the Wednesday Addams playbook

145
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:25,648
and take a break from romance.

146
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:31,696
It's not very fun

147
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:34,823
to be tied up and treated like a pet...

148
00:09:36,283 --> 00:09:37,284
is it?

149
00:09:37,784 --> 00:09:39,494
"Mystery meat sandwich!"

150
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:41,121
"Your favorite."

151
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:44,164
Conserve your energy.

152
00:09:44,165 --> 00:09:45,418
You're gonna need it.

153
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:50,965
I wish I was at least
in one of these pictures.

154
00:09:53,717 --> 00:09:57,263
I never understood
your desire for a Normie life.

155
00:09:59,097 --> 00:10:03,269
But... knowing what Stonehurst
did to you in that lab...

156
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:08,941
Neither of us got
the end that we deserved.

157
00:10:10,817 --> 00:10:12,403
That changes tonight.

158
00:10:16,782 --> 00:10:17,823
Promise me,

159
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:19,743
no matter what happens,

160
00:10:19,744 --> 00:10:20,911
you'll do it.

161
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:22,913
What we discussed.

162
00:10:25,081 --> 00:10:26,375
I need your word.

163
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:35,674
I made Hyde tracks about 20 miles north
and dropped Pugsley's costume,

164
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:37,927
then made an anonymous tip like you said.

165
00:10:38,428 --> 00:10:40,346
Good, huh?

166
00:10:40,347 --> 00:10:42,890
That'll keep the cops off our trail.

167
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:47,854
Now, it's time to position
your old flame onto the board.

168
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:49,773
Wednesday will know she's being played.

169
00:10:49,774 --> 00:10:53,567
Yeah, an Addams...
would never sacrifice one of their own.

170
00:10:53,568 --> 00:10:55,153
Not even a pawn.

171
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:58,532
And that emotional weakness

172
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:01,034
will be our checkmate.

173
00:11:02,702 --> 00:11:03,912
[Enid] Any Pugsley update?

174
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:06,206
Still missing. But he's alive.

175
00:11:06,206 --> 00:11:08,375
Isaac is hellbent on saving his sister.

176
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:11,628
I know he needs Pugsley.
Just need to figure out when and where.

177
00:11:11,629 --> 00:11:13,754
[Agnes] Crap. He's here.

178
00:11:13,755 --> 00:11:14,756
Who?

179
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:16,549
[Enid] Isaac?

180
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:18,802
No. My dad.

181
00:11:18,802 --> 00:11:21,888
He usually sends
some rando assistant to collect me.

182
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:23,722
Your mom couldn't come get you?

183
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:26,851
She's busy with
her new Normie husband and baby.

184
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:29,979
I was the mistake
that kept her and my dad together

185
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:31,523
long past their sell-by date.

186
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:33,359
Gunpowder, penicillin, the rack.

187
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:35,528
Those were all mistakes.

188
00:11:36,986 --> 00:11:39,989
I just want to say that I love us.

189
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:41,448
We're like the three musketeers.

190
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:42,450
Careful.

191
00:11:42,451 --> 00:11:43,536
[Agnes's dad] Agnes!

192
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:46,038
Bye. See you next year.

193
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:49,915
I wish I could help,
but I have to get to the Lupin cages.

194
00:11:49,917 --> 00:11:51,584
Capri read me the riot act.

195
00:11:51,585 --> 00:11:53,419
Lock in early and stay calm.

196
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:56,213
So I have my meditation app,
my fave playlist,

197
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:58,466
and an extra supply of colloidal silver.

198
00:11:58,466 --> 00:11:59,842
[breathes deeply]

199
00:11:59,844 --> 00:12:01,595
What could go wrong, right?

200
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:04,514
I'll be there
first thing in the morning to let you out.

201
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:07,017
Promise?

202
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:10,645
[chuckles softly]

203
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:13,355
You. We're waking the dead again.

204
00:12:13,356 --> 00:12:15,357
How long until
your corpse moths are airborne?

205
00:12:15,359 --> 00:12:17,693
Unfortunately,
they're permanently grounded.

206
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:20,447
Corpse moths only have
a 36-hour life cycle.

207
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:24,491
Wednesday, I'm really sorry.

208
00:12:24,493 --> 00:12:26,536
Pugsley wanted to be my friend
and I blew him off.

209
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:29,080
Maybe if I'd been nicer,
he wouldn't have felt the need

210
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:30,831
to become BFFs with a zombie.

211
00:12:30,832 --> 00:12:32,584
I am my brother's keeper.

212
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:34,793
I simply should have caged him
for his own protection.

213
00:12:34,794 --> 00:12:38,130
I'm heading to the Hummer shed.
Have to hibernate my bees early.

214
00:12:38,131 --> 00:12:39,466
Wanna come...

215
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:41,927
[bees buzzing]

216
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:46,347
["Miss You" by the Rapture
playing over radio]

217
00:12:48,017 --> 00:12:50,019
[upbeat dance-punk song continuing]

218
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:52,687
[Eugene gasps]

219
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:55,024
[chilling music playing]

220
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:58,652
[music crescendos, trails off]

221
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:04,072
Wednesday,
I'm on my way to see your parents.

222
00:13:04,073 --> 00:13:05,783
A hiker found Pugsley's costume.

223
00:13:05,784 --> 00:13:08,577
I'm redeploying the search
from Jericho to Burlington.

224
00:13:08,578 --> 00:13:10,456
Sounds like a ploy
to draw you off the scent.

225
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:13,458
I follow evidence, not hunches.

226
00:13:14,835 --> 00:13:17,212
Finally, I get my office back.

227
00:13:18,422 --> 00:13:22,424
Dort's crashing downfall
has validated my legacy.

228
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:26,428
The board will now look back upon
the Weems era with fondness.

229
00:13:26,429 --> 00:13:30,225
Nevermore clearly needs
a steady hand on the rudder.

230
00:13:30,225 --> 00:13:33,186
A leader of impeccable moral character.

231
00:13:33,187 --> 00:13:35,648
You covered up Rowan's murder
and the existence of a Hyde.

232
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:38,525
Mistakes were made.

233
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:41,152
But that's all in the past.

234
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:43,279
[footsteps approaching]

235
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,325
I went out to the Hummers shed.

236
00:13:47,326 --> 00:13:49,869
Slurp was there,
except he looks totally human.

237
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:51,037
He told me to give you this.

238
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:54,499
Said if I breathe a word to anyone else,
he'd come for me.

239
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,417
Wednesday, I'm scared.

240
00:13:56,418 --> 00:13:58,546
Go back to your dorm. Lock the door.

241
00:13:59,129 --> 00:14:00,129
Now!

242
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:05,344
[dire, suspenseful music playing]

243
00:14:22,861 --> 00:14:25,905
Isaac thinks he can
lure me out to finish me off.

244
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:28,116
[muffled struggling]

245
00:14:30,702 --> 00:14:32,580
When you get a clear shot...

246
00:14:34,789 --> 00:14:36,750
put a bolt in his zombie brain.

247
00:14:49,971 --> 00:14:51,639
Tyler warned me you were formidable.

248
00:14:51,639 --> 00:14:55,475
And now I've witnessed
the havoc you can wreak.

249
00:14:55,476 --> 00:14:58,938
Give me my brother, crawl back
into your hole, and stay dead this time.

250
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:02,275
- I know what you did to my father.
- Yet I'm the one who died.

251
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:05,236
Thanks to him and your dear mother.

252
00:15:05,904 --> 00:15:09,698
Why don't you let your brother
pay for their mistakes,

253
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:10,783
and we'll call it even?

254
00:15:10,783 --> 00:15:12,327
You don't have the machine.

255
00:15:12,827 --> 00:15:14,620
Willow Hill and Iago Tower
have been destroyed.

256
00:15:14,621 --> 00:15:16,538
It would take months to rebuild.

257
00:15:16,539 --> 00:15:19,208
By the time you did,
it'd be too late to save your sister.

258
00:15:24,213 --> 00:15:26,090
I... I applaud the effort.

259
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:27,383
You keep me talking

260
00:15:27,384 --> 00:15:29,970
while your faithful right hand
takes his shot.

261
00:15:34,307 --> 00:15:35,308
Gotcha.

262
00:15:41,230 --> 00:15:43,192
Except he's never been yours.

263
00:15:44,317 --> 00:15:45,193
He's mine.

264
00:15:46,778 --> 00:15:49,740
Turns out your parents
didn't kill all of me that night.

265
00:16:07,924 --> 00:16:08,966
Cute.

266
00:16:08,967 --> 00:16:11,302
Imagine my surprise
when I saw my right hand

267
00:16:11,302 --> 00:16:14,054
wandering the halls
of Willow Hill without me.

268
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:18,059
And a DaVinci...
is nothing without his right hand.

269
00:16:21,813 --> 00:16:24,566
<i>Your mother cut it off.</i>

270
00:16:29,153 --> 00:16:33,826
<i>Causing my machine
to go out of control and explode.</i>

271
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:38,120
The power surge must have
somehow animated my hand.

272
00:16:38,121 --> 00:16:40,374
In your case,
the part is greater than the whole.

273
00:16:57,099 --> 00:16:59,100
[ghastly, suspenseful music playing]

274
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:18,412
Now I am complete.

275
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:27,128
The Addams family

276
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:30,257
ends tonight.

277
00:17:32,550 --> 00:17:34,135
Starting with you.

278
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:04,957
[Isaac] We have
an appointment at Iago Tower.

279
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:08,628
Your pathetic little life
will finally have a purpose.

280
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:11,632
[Pugsley struggling in distance]

281
00:18:14,218 --> 00:18:15,219
[gasps]

282
00:18:19,765 --> 00:18:20,765
[sighs]

283
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,851
[gentle, fraught music playing]

284
00:18:34,445 --> 00:18:35,822
[screams excitedly]

285
00:18:35,823 --> 00:18:38,200
[both chuckle happily]

286
00:18:38,866 --> 00:18:41,744
Now we can finally fix our family.

287
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:43,288
Hello!

288
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:47,459
- Come on.
- [Pugsley grunts]

289
00:18:49,877 --> 00:18:53,213
[meditation app guide]
<i>Take a deep breath in, and slowly exhale.</i>

290
00:18:53,214 --> 00:18:55,423
<i>Now visualize the wolf within.</i>

291
00:18:55,424 --> 00:18:57,926
<i>A powerful but gentle spirit.</i>

292
00:18:57,927 --> 00:19:00,721
<i>Be mindful that tonight
belongs to tranquility...</i>

293
00:19:00,721 --> 00:19:02,056
Enid! I need you.

294
00:19:02,057 --> 00:19:05,726
- Agnes? I thought you left.
- I couldn't abandon Wednesday.

295
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:07,980
So I ditched my dad
when he stopped for gas.

296
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:10,897
Isaac buried Wednesday
under the Skull Tree.

297
00:19:10,898 --> 00:19:11,983
And I can't dig her out.

298
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:14,652
What? Oh my God.

299
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:16,612
- Where's Thing?
- Longer story.

300
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:19,700
I'll fill you in on the way.
We haven't got much time!

301
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:22,034
[rousing, suspenseful music playing]

302
00:19:22,035 --> 00:19:24,163
[Enid] Wednesday, we're here! Hang on!

303
00:19:28,291 --> 00:19:30,001
I hear a heartbeat, but it's weak.

304
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:39,970
We aren't gonna get to her in time.

305
00:19:40,511 --> 00:19:42,681
No, no, no.

306
00:19:45,474 --> 00:19:48,019
[dramatic choral music playing]

307
00:19:49,938 --> 00:19:51,565
[Enid] I'm not strong enough like this.

308
00:19:54,317 --> 00:19:55,943
You won't be able to turn back.

309
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:57,778
You're an Alpha.

310
00:19:58,529 --> 00:19:59,865
I can't let her die.

311
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:04,827
[Enid crying out]

312
00:20:06,371 --> 00:20:07,372
[Enid snarling]

313
00:20:19,884 --> 00:20:23,387
[Agnes panting]

314
00:20:24,847 --> 00:20:28,143
Wednesday, wake up. Wake up!

315
00:20:34,691 --> 00:20:36,401
Please. Please.

316
00:20:39,028 --> 00:20:40,029
I enjoyed that.

317
00:20:45,451 --> 00:20:46,452
Enid?

318
00:20:50,123 --> 00:20:51,959
It was the only way to save you.

319
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,344
[snarling]

320
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:05,596
Go track her. Now!

321
00:21:07,098 --> 00:21:09,101
[Morticia breathlessly]
Wednesday! Wednesday!

322
00:21:10,559 --> 00:21:12,436
Thank the spirits.

323
00:21:15,523 --> 00:21:16,692
Or just one in particular.

324
00:21:17,358 --> 00:21:20,486
If you don't hurry,
you'll have nothing left to save.

325
00:21:20,487 --> 00:21:21,946
Where's Pugsley?

326
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:37,086
It's all still here.

327
00:21:39,839 --> 00:21:40,673
Good.

328
00:21:40,673 --> 00:21:43,134
How are we gonna put
this junk back together?

329
00:21:43,134 --> 00:21:44,302
[Isaac] We're not.

330
00:21:46,512 --> 00:21:47,513
I am.

331
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:54,020
["Toccata and Fugue in D minor"
by Bach playing over gramophone]

332
00:22:22,548 --> 00:22:25,425
Even if you never told me
the truth about Thing,

333
00:22:25,426 --> 00:22:26,926
why didn't you tell him?

334
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:29,512
Because sometimes
the truth is better left buried.

335
00:22:29,513 --> 00:22:31,223
Thing had no memory of Isaac.

336
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:36,145
<i>After everything Isaac did to your father,
why burden Thing with that knowledge?</i>

337
00:22:36,771 --> 00:22:40,816
I like to think whatever trace of goodness
was in Isaac somehow ended up in Thing.

338
00:22:40,817 --> 00:22:44,111
Except now he's reattached to Isaac,
and he's about to kill your son.

339
00:22:44,112 --> 00:22:46,905
[grandiose organ music
continuing in distance]

340
00:22:46,906 --> 00:22:49,032
Mad scientist, clichÃ© soundtrack.

341
00:22:49,034 --> 00:22:50,034
Perfect.

342
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:50,993
Darling,

343
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:53,578
you call the sheriff.

344
00:22:53,579 --> 00:22:55,374
Leave this to us.

345
00:22:56,665 --> 00:22:58,460
<i>Querida</i>, save our boy.

346
00:23:12,766 --> 00:23:14,768
[machinery thrumming]

347
00:23:29,532 --> 00:23:30,909
[music trails off]

348
00:23:33,452 --> 00:23:34,787
Isaac, are you all right?

349
00:23:34,788 --> 00:23:36,788
I'm fine. [inhales deeply]

350
00:23:36,789 --> 00:23:38,500
Secure the power source.

351
00:23:53,932 --> 00:23:57,268
I've been waiting
for this moment for 30 years.

352
00:23:57,269 --> 00:23:58,644
[muffled grunting]

353
00:24:15,953 --> 00:24:17,203
Get ready.

354
00:24:17,204 --> 00:24:19,249
We're about to fry your battery.

355
00:24:30,926 --> 00:24:32,304
It's time, Isaac.

356
00:24:33,221 --> 00:24:34,055
Do it now.

357
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:37,642
Now!

358
00:24:38,393 --> 00:24:39,728
You promised me.

359
00:24:57,828 --> 00:24:59,580
[Tyler] Wait! What are you doing?

360
00:25:00,624 --> 00:25:02,458
Mom, we're here to save you.

361
00:25:02,459 --> 00:25:04,461
It's too late for me, sweetie.

362
00:25:05,045 --> 00:25:06,836
This is your time now.

363
00:25:06,837 --> 00:25:09,132
We can save you from this life.

364
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:12,134
Give you a fresh start.

365
00:25:13,094 --> 00:25:16,013
No, no, you have no right
to take my power from me!

366
00:25:19,476 --> 00:25:20,644
Love you.

367
00:25:21,644 --> 00:25:23,686
Don't do this. Please.

368
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:24,980
I love you, baby.

369
00:25:27,733 --> 00:25:29,234
[foreboding music playing]

370
00:25:29,236 --> 00:25:31,238
[machinery humming]

371
00:25:34,950 --> 00:25:35,866
[Tyler wails] Mom!

372
00:25:36,992 --> 00:25:39,913
You take the main staircase.
I'll take the ladder.

373
00:25:45,042 --> 00:25:46,294
[Tyler] Mom, please!

374
00:25:49,631 --> 00:25:50,673
Mom!

375
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:55,427
We have company.

376
00:25:56,179 --> 00:25:57,806
[Tyler] Please, don't do this!

377
00:25:58,847 --> 00:26:00,808
[thrumming intensifies]

378
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:02,227
[screams]

379
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:06,730
[energy crackling]

380
00:26:21,371 --> 00:26:22,705
[painful yelling]

381
00:26:27,876 --> 00:26:30,755
[boys moan painfully]

382
00:26:40,181 --> 00:26:41,473
Kill me.

383
00:26:42,224 --> 00:26:44,059
[music crescendos, trails off]

384
00:26:47,646 --> 00:26:48,690
[crackling slows down]

385
00:26:51,859 --> 00:26:53,987
- Why?
- I missed.

386
00:26:59,576 --> 00:27:00,826
[Tyler roaring]

387
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:10,502
Tyler, no!

388
00:27:11,086 --> 00:27:12,212
No!

389
00:27:16,425 --> 00:27:18,345
Isaac!

390
00:27:19,721 --> 00:27:20,846
Isaac!

391
00:27:21,806 --> 00:27:22,807
Isaac.

392
00:27:28,355 --> 00:27:29,229
[Francoise] It's okay.

393
00:27:29,230 --> 00:27:31,105
- [muffled] Wednesday?
- Shh.

394
00:27:31,106 --> 00:27:32,482
[Francoise] It's your mommy.

395
00:27:32,483 --> 00:27:36,363
I haven't enjoyed a mother-son
relationship like this since <i>Psycho.</i>

396
00:27:42,576 --> 00:27:44,328
Tyler? Honey?

397
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:47,914
Baby...

398
00:27:47,915 --> 00:27:49,000
[Francoise yells]

399
00:27:52,753 --> 00:27:53,961
[snarling]

400
00:27:53,962 --> 00:27:55,757
[foreboding music continuing]

401
00:28:17,112 --> 00:28:18,113
[moaning weakly]

402
00:28:20,531 --> 00:28:22,409
Hold on, Pugsley. Hold on.

403
00:28:42,679 --> 00:28:44,847
[both snarling]

404
00:29:19,048 --> 00:29:19,883
[yelps]

405
00:29:30,309 --> 00:29:32,311
[deep bellowing]

406
00:29:37,232 --> 00:29:38,358
Isaac!

407
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:41,779
You have something that belongs to me.

408
00:29:42,905 --> 00:29:44,907
[music builds]

409
00:29:45,741 --> 00:29:46,826
Come on! Come on!

410
00:29:48,619 --> 00:29:50,246
[music halts]

411
00:30:02,090 --> 00:30:04,093
[forlorn, emotional music playing]

412
00:30:19,776 --> 00:30:20,777
[Santiago] Go.

413
00:30:21,944 --> 00:30:23,403
Go, go, go!

414
00:30:28,535 --> 00:30:30,537
[dark, imposing music playing]

415
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:36,750
[Tyler bellowing]

416
00:30:40,171 --> 00:30:41,172
[music trailing off]

417
00:30:44,259 --> 00:30:46,260
[somber, distraught music playing]

418
00:31:01,901 --> 00:31:03,443
[Pugsley] Mom. Dad.

419
00:31:06,573 --> 00:31:07,740
Tish!

420
00:31:10,576 --> 00:31:11,577
[gasps sharply]

421
00:31:15,832 --> 00:31:18,209
[Gomez] Help me. Help me with this.

422
00:31:32,347 --> 00:31:35,393
I guess your premonition
didn't come true after all.

423
00:31:46,820 --> 00:31:48,779
[Isaac] Because of you,

424
00:31:48,780 --> 00:31:51,700
I lost the only person I ever truly loved.

425
00:31:51,701 --> 00:31:54,162
[Gomez] Isaac! Isaac!

426
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:55,913
It's over.

427
00:31:55,913 --> 00:31:57,330
Let my daughter go.

428
00:31:57,332 --> 00:31:58,999
Sorry, old friend.

429
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:02,502
Now you two will know
what real pain feels like.

430
00:32:04,212 --> 00:32:06,798
One more step, and I snap her neck!

431
00:32:11,679 --> 00:32:14,765
Thing, we know you're still in there.

432
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:16,893
Come back to us, Thing. We love you.

433
00:32:17,602 --> 00:32:19,060
We're your family!

434
00:32:19,061 --> 00:32:21,271
This was never part of your family.

435
00:32:22,105 --> 00:32:23,231
It's a part of me!

436
00:32:30,906 --> 00:32:32,659
[gasping for breath]

437
00:32:38,205 --> 00:32:39,539
You missed!

438
00:32:40,208 --> 00:32:41,209
[bones cracking]

439
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:47,382
[tense, eerie music playing]

440
00:32:48,715 --> 00:32:50,093
Come on, Thing.

441
00:32:52,010 --> 00:32:54,012
[dramatic, frenetic music playing]

442
00:33:00,686 --> 00:33:01,770
What is happening?

443
00:33:04,356 --> 00:33:06,651
- Ah!
- Doesn't take a genius to figure that out.

444
00:33:11,239 --> 00:33:13,115
[grunting]

445
00:33:26,045 --> 00:33:27,087
[Isaac whimpering]

446
00:33:45,147 --> 00:33:46,148
[heart ticking]

447
00:33:47,525 --> 00:33:48,526
[crying out]

448
00:33:53,197 --> 00:33:54,115
Time's up.

449
00:34:14,260 --> 00:34:15,762
[dramatic music trailing off]

450
00:34:22,018 --> 00:34:24,019
[gentle, aching music playing]

451
00:35:04,476 --> 00:35:05,811
[Wednesday] Welcome back, Thing.

452
00:35:07,188 --> 00:35:10,440
- [Pugsley chuckles softly]
- [Gomez giggles]

453
00:35:21,869 --> 00:35:23,871
[somber, introspective music playing]

454
00:35:35,382 --> 00:35:38,344
Knowing you were cut from
the literal cloth of an evil genius,

455
00:35:38,969 --> 00:35:40,804
it makes sense why we're so compatible.

456
00:35:42,931 --> 00:35:44,684
How does it feel
finally knowing the truth?

457
00:35:47,311 --> 00:35:51,273
That you can't control the past.
But the future is in your own hand.

458
00:35:54,860 --> 00:35:56,195
What's it going to be?

459
00:36:05,454 --> 00:36:06,581
[whooshing]

460
00:36:07,748 --> 00:36:11,293
- What have you been able to figure out?
- This was on a wildlife cam this morning.

461
00:36:13,378 --> 00:36:14,630
[Wednesday] That's Enid.

462
00:36:15,213 --> 00:36:16,715
[Agnes] She was heading north,

463
00:36:16,715 --> 00:36:18,925
just five miles from the Canadian border.

464
00:36:18,925 --> 00:36:20,177
What about Capri?

465
00:36:20,177 --> 00:36:23,346
Was she able to provide intel
that could tell us where Enid is going?

466
00:36:23,347 --> 00:36:24,764
She's MIA.

467
00:36:24,764 --> 00:36:27,099
Probably on the hunt for her next job,

468
00:36:27,101 --> 00:36:30,146
now that Nevermore is nevermore.

469
00:36:38,778 --> 00:36:40,239
[Capri] Hello, Tyler.

470
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:44,659
Whoever you are, just walk away.

471
00:36:47,121 --> 00:36:50,166
We both know
you can't survive out here alone.

472
00:36:50,916 --> 00:36:52,335
Not for long.

473
00:36:53,668 --> 00:36:55,211
But I can save you.

474
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:57,838
[mysterious, intriguing music playing]

475
00:36:57,840 --> 00:37:00,592
Yeah, I'm done with mothers and masters.

476
00:37:00,592 --> 00:37:03,094
I'm not interested in being either.

477
00:37:06,264 --> 00:37:07,474
I'm offering...

478
00:37:08,391 --> 00:37:11,686
a support system for people just like you.

479
00:37:11,686 --> 00:37:13,438
Fellow Hydes,

480
00:37:13,438 --> 00:37:16,275
hidden away where
the world can't find them.

481
00:37:19,277 --> 00:37:20,695
You'd be part of a pack,

482
00:37:21,947 --> 00:37:26,327
creating a bond that transcends
the need for a single master.

483
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:33,833
What's in it for you?

484
00:37:33,833 --> 00:37:36,878
You're a werewolf.
I can smell it from here.

485
00:37:38,338 --> 00:37:39,923
My father was a Hyde.

486
00:37:43,844 --> 00:37:45,137
[sighs glumly]

487
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:52,184
This isn't gonna
explode in my face, is it?

488
00:37:52,186 --> 00:37:53,688
A little snack for the road.

489
00:37:57,023 --> 00:37:58,733
Don't forget to pace yourself.

490
00:37:58,733 --> 00:38:00,987
Whoa. Thanks.

491
00:38:01,487 --> 00:38:03,445
You know, I was thinking,

492
00:38:03,447 --> 00:38:06,074
over the break, if you're not too busy,

493
00:38:06,074 --> 00:38:07,659
you could come for a visit?

494
00:38:08,827 --> 00:38:10,871
Really? To your actual house?

495
00:38:11,539 --> 00:38:13,331
That's what friends do, right?

496
00:38:18,003 --> 00:38:19,170
Hmm.

497
00:38:20,213 --> 00:38:21,257
Wednesday.

498
00:38:23,009 --> 00:38:24,010
Wait.

499
00:38:25,844 --> 00:38:27,887
I would like you to have something.

500
00:38:30,349 --> 00:38:31,599
Aunt Ophelia's journal.

501
00:38:31,599 --> 00:38:32,684
Yes.

502
00:38:33,436 --> 00:38:35,144
As I keep being reminded,

503
00:38:35,146 --> 00:38:38,273
harboring secrets can have
deadly consequences.

504
00:38:39,358 --> 00:38:41,860
Every family has dark chapters, Wednesday.

505
00:38:43,945 --> 00:38:45,447
Including ours.

506
00:38:46,574 --> 00:38:47,657
Thank you, Mother.

507
00:38:49,492 --> 00:38:51,827
It's gratifying to see you two together.

508
00:38:51,829 --> 00:38:53,788
[somber, enchanting music playing]

509
00:38:53,789 --> 00:38:56,206
Restoring your familial bond

510
00:38:56,208 --> 00:38:59,378
was the first big step
in regaining your psychic ability.

511
00:39:01,422 --> 00:39:05,259
Now that it's happened,
I'm taking a well-deserved sabbatical.

512
00:39:11,389 --> 00:39:16,478
Whoever thought that the person
to keep my spirit alive would be you?

513
00:39:18,898 --> 00:39:20,940
Until we meet again, Wednesday.

514
00:39:32,577 --> 00:39:34,496
[Gomez] Whoa, it's sunny out there.

515
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:38,708
It will be a relief
sleeping under our own leaky roof tonight.

516
00:39:39,793 --> 00:39:42,295
Oh, let's get your things. <i>Vamos.</i>

517
00:39:42,295 --> 00:39:43,545
I won't be going home.

518
00:39:43,547 --> 00:39:46,382
["Walk Don't Run" by the Surfaris playing]

519
00:39:46,384 --> 00:39:49,135
[rowdy surf rock continuing]

520
00:39:57,103 --> 00:39:58,811
[chortling] I got your message.

521
00:39:58,813 --> 00:40:00,813
I'm always up for a road trip.

522
00:40:00,815 --> 00:40:03,525
So where to?
Slaughter Beach? Death Valley?

523
00:40:03,525 --> 00:40:05,652
We're headed north to rescue Enid.

524
00:40:06,362 --> 00:40:07,612
She's an Alpha.

525
00:40:07,612 --> 00:40:11,240
Ooh, I hear those puppies got fangs
that can rip you apart like taffy,

526
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:13,992
and claws that can
slice you up like lunch meat.

527
00:40:13,994 --> 00:40:14,994
What fun!

528
00:40:14,994 --> 00:40:16,371
Go.

529
00:40:23,878 --> 00:40:27,048
[Wednesday] <i>Another year at Nevermore
ends in carnage and chaos.</i>

530
00:40:28,217 --> 00:40:30,677
<i>Unanswered questions hover like vultures.</i>

531
00:40:30,677 --> 00:40:34,431
["Sweet Dreams (String Version)"
by the Hampton Rock String Quartet plays]

532
00:40:35,766 --> 00:40:39,351
<i>Why did I slice Tyler's bonds
rather than his jugular?</i>

533
00:40:39,353 --> 00:40:41,938
<i>And will that impulsive
act of mercy become my undoing?</i>

534
00:40:44,775 --> 00:40:48,193
<i>As for my parents,
their smiles don't erase their lies.</i>

535
00:40:48,195 --> 00:40:50,155
[dark, moody arrangement continuing]

536
00:40:52,115 --> 00:40:55,161
<i>Was my mother's gift
of Ophelia's diary an act of trust,</i>

537
00:40:56,161 --> 00:40:57,871
<i>or silent desperation?</i>

538
00:41:02,251 --> 00:41:04,043
<i>First I must find Enid.</i>

539
00:41:06,963 --> 00:41:08,423
<i>I gave her my word.</i>

540
00:41:08,965 --> 00:41:11,510
<i>But who exactly will return by my side?</i>

541
00:41:13,344 --> 00:41:14,679
<i>My friend?</i>

542
00:41:15,222 --> 00:41:17,307
<i>Or the beast that's consumed her?</i>

543
00:41:22,730 --> 00:41:24,063
[jarring stinger]

544
00:41:32,030 --> 00:41:33,199
Aunt Ophelia.

545
00:41:34,115 --> 00:41:36,117
[dark, moody arrangement continuing]

546
00:41:43,958 --> 00:41:46,378
<i>Secrets are the bedrock
of the Addams family.</i>

547
00:41:48,213 --> 00:41:50,882
<i>Toxic and festering
just below the surface.</i>

548
00:42:01,936 --> 00:42:03,269
[Hester] Ophelia!

549
00:42:08,943 --> 00:42:11,360
[Wednesday] <i>As I venture into the unknown,</i>

550
00:42:11,362 --> 00:42:14,572
<i>I am determined to exhume
every lie and deception,</i>

551
00:42:15,157 --> 00:42:16,449
<i>or die trying.</i>

552
00:42:17,617 --> 00:42:20,369
<i>Sounds like a perfect vacation to me.</i>

553
00:42:20,371 --> 00:42:21,454
[raven caws]

554
00:42:22,164 --> 00:42:24,166
[jauntily macabre outro music playing]
